{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product 2023 * n. Since n can be any positive integer, this is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of any multiple of 2023. This is a problem of finding the smallest Hamming weight of a multiple of a given integer.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Analyze the number 2023 in binary. Determine its prime factorization and check if it is coprime to 2. Note that 2023 = 7 * 17^2. Since 2023 is odd, there exists an integer n such that 2023 * n = 2^m - 1 for some m, or more generally, 2023 * n can be represented as a sum of powers of 2."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate if k(n) = 1 is possible. This would require 2023 * n = 2^m for some m. Determine if 2023 divides any power of 2. If not, k(n) must be greater than 1."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_3",
      "instructions": "Investigate if k(n) = 2 is possible. This would require 2023 * n = 2^a + 2^b for some integers a > b >= 0. This is equivalent to checking if 2023 divides 2^b * (2^(a-b) + 1). Since 2023 is odd, this is equivalent to checking if 2023 divides 2^k + 1 for some k. Check the order of 2 modulo 2023 or its factors (7 and 289) to see if 2^k is congruent to -1 modulo 2023."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_4",
      "instructions": "If k(n) = 2 is impossible, investigate if k(n) = 3 is possible. This requires 2023 to divide 2^a + 2^b + 2^c. Check if there exist integers a, b, c such that 2^a + 2^b + 2^c is a multiple of 2023. This is equivalent to checking if 2^x + 2^y + 1 is congruent to 0 modulo 2023 for some x, y."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent node should first confirm that k(n) cannot be 1 because 2023 is not a power of 2. Then, evaluate the possibility of k(n) = 2 by checking if 2^k is congruent to -1 modulo 2023 (or 2^k is congruent to 1 modulo 2023 with specific parity conditions). If k(n) = 2 is ruled out, test for k(n) = 3 by checking if the sum of three powers of 2 can be a multiple of 2023. The smallest k(n) found among these cases is the final answer."
}

